# Cypress E2E vs Vitest

Do **not** add a Cypress test for every small UI change. Prefer a thin E2E suite; put most coverage in Vitest + Testing Library.

## Use Cypress when

- Protecting a **critical user journey** end-to-end (e.g. login → create → save → see result)
- Behavior depends on **routing, auth, Firebase, network**, or real browser behavior
- Guarding a regression unit tests cannot catch (full page load, redirects, cookies)
- Adding/updating a **smoke** that the app boots and a main route renders

## Prefer Vitest / Testing Library when

- Component render, props, local UI state, validation messages
- Copy/layout/styling tweaks (often no new test; update existing component test only if assertion must change)
- Fast feedback while iterating on isolated UI

## Do not

- Add one Cypress spec per PR or per UI polish
- Assert spacing, colors, or decorative layout in E2E
- Duplicate the same assertion in both Cypress and Vitest when one layer is enough (component for render; Cypress for the journey)

## Decision table

| Change | Test layer |
|--------|------------|
| Spacing, colors, minor copy | Usually none; update Vitest only if an existing assertion breaks |
| Form field / component behavior | Vitest + Testing Library |
| New feature critical path | **One** Cypress journey covering the path (not every UI detail) |
| Refactor with same UX | Keep existing E2E; do not expand the suite |

## Repo conventions (`tanstack-app`)

- Component/unit: colocated `*.test.tsx` with Vitest (see `src/components/Home.test.tsx`)
- E2E: `cypress/e2e/*.cy.ts`; run via `pnpm test:e2e` / `pnpm cy:run`
- Default for new work: Vitest first; Cypress only for smoke or a high-value journey

```typescript
// ✅ Vitest — component renders correctly
expect(screen.getByRole('heading', { name: m.home_welcome() })).toBeTruthy()

// ✅ Cypress — thin smoke / journey
cy.visit('/')
cy.contains('h1', '...').should('be.visible')

// ❌ Cypress for every Button padding / label tweak
```
